  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhance Border Management and Social Cohesion at the Borders of C&#xF4;te d&apos;Ivoire with Mali and Burkina Faso</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project supports the local communities in the border areas in the northern part of C&#xF4;te d&apos;Ivoire in order to enhance effective border management and build trust among security agents, local authorities and the populations. The overall objective is to further consolidate the notion of constructed border posts and raising awareness of living in the sensitive border zones. This project will include training for government stakeholders on the Migration Information and Data Analysis System, awareness raising activities for local populations in Minignan (Ti&#xE9;finzo border post), Tengr&#xE9;la (Ningouni border post) and Doropo (Kogui&#xE9;nou border post) and a one-day humanitarian crisis simulation exercise in either Minignan area or Tengr&#xE9;la area.</narrative>
  </description>
